# CI failure logs — use `gh`, not the Actions web page

The GitHub Actions job page often **does not expose full logs** to agents or unsigned viewers (“Sign in to view logs”). Do **not** guess the failure from the page summary alone.

When the user links a run or job (e.g. `https://github.com/AlexsanderHamir/Hamix/actions/runs/27997390975/job/82862345777`), **fetch logs with the GitHub CLI** in the shell.

## Workflow

1. **Prefer local reproduction first** — see `.cursor/rules/verification.mdc` (`.\scripts\check.ps1` / `./scripts/check.sh`, scoped `--group=` when applicable).
2. **When CI failed and the user shared a URL**, extract the **run ID** from the path (`/actions/runs/<RUN_ID>/...`).
3. **Pull failed-step output** with `gh` (repo defaults to `origin` when run from this clone):

```bash
# Run summary + per-job conclusions
gh run view <RUN_ID> --repo AlexsanderHamir/Hamix --json conclusion,status,displayTitle,headSha,jobs

# Failed steps only (primary source for root cause)
gh run view <RUN_ID> --repo AlexsanderHamir/Hamix --log-failed
```

On Windows PowerShell, pipe the log tail if output is large:

```powershell
gh run view <RUN_ID> --repo AlexsanderHamir/Hamix --log-failed 2>&1 | Select-Object -Last 120
```

4. **Report**: which job/matrix cell failed, failing package/test names, and the last error lines — not just “exit code 1”.

## Do not

- Do **not** use `gh run watch` or poll Actions as the main fix loop (see `verification.mdc`).
- Do **not** claim you cannot see CI details without trying `gh run view --log-failed` first.

## Example (run 27997390975, commit `3b480e5`)

| Job | Result |
| --- | --- |
| `go-lint`, `go-tests (core\|tasks\|agents)`, `web` | passed |
| **`go-tests (harness)`** | **failed** (~10m) |

Harness failures: tasks stuck at `status="ready"`; logs showed `agent worker task missing git binding; deferring pickup`. Harness tests need `worktree_id` / `branch_id` on seeded tasks (same class of fix as `pkgs/tasks/agentreconcile/git_test_helpers_test.go`).
